// @check
// @error-at 7:5 A type alias requires a body; write `type Foo = …` to define `Foo`
// A bodyless `type Foo` (grammar alt `TYPE ID`, no `= body`) has no meaning
// today — opaque/recursive aliases are unsupported (ROADMAP A14). It must report
// cleanly AT THE DECLARATION, naming the alias and suggesting the `= { … }` fix,
// rather than silently aliasing the name to itself and only surfacing a confusing
// "refers to itself" error at each use site.
type Foo
let x: Foo = 0
